debugger-ui-ncurses — Phase 6: ncurses UI (cl-charms / PDCurses)
================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 6)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (§19)
  issues/open/debugger-ui-protocol-and-dumb.issue (prerequisite — Phase 5)

Context
-------

The ncurses UI is Strandh's four-pane layout in a terminal. It is a
refinement of the dumb-terminal UI against the same `clautolisp.debug.ui`
protocol; no new debugger-engine capability is required.

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. New system `clautolisp/autolisp-debug-ui-tui`, package `clautolisp.ui.tui`:
   a thin abstraction layer wrapping cl-charms (Unix) and PDCurses-via-CFFI
   (Windows), selected per platform (spec §19.3). 8-colour fallback; mouse
   optional; key-only navigation MUST be complete.

2. Four-pane layout (spec §19.1): stack (top-left), source (top-right),
   interactor/commands (bottom-left), repl/eval-in-frame (bottom-right).
   Source pane shows poll-point (blue) / breakpoint (red) / current (yellow)
   markers; click or `b`-then-Enter toggles a breakpoint. Configurable layout.

3. Inspector pane (spec §19.2): replaces the source pane (push/pop); header
   shows origin + path, footer lists actions; Enter descends, Backspace
   ascends, p copies path (OSC 52 where supported), b binds, e -> repl, q closes.

4. Event loop in the UI thread ONLY; debugger-thread notifications funnelled
   through a queue and dispatched on refresh — no curses call off the UI thread.

Acceptance
----------

- Keyboard-only break/step/inspect session in a real terminal; 8-colour mode;
  marker colours correct; inspector pane push/pop works.
- New cl-charms dependency wired into the system.
- FiveAM tests where feasible (logic layer); `*version*` bumped.

* Resolution (triage 2026-07-23)

Shipped: four-pane ncurses-ui.lisp + tui/tui-charms layers with inspector pane and tests. The PDCurses/Windows backend stays deferred (platform-bound, tracked in the windows packaging work).
